Program: Outlook
Title: 02/07/2009
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p003jd67
Last Broadcast Date: Thu 2 Jul 2009
Matthew Bannister presents personal stories behind the news from all over the world. On today's programme: Heroin in Zanzibar; New Australians; Death row artist; Save our sounds. Heroin addiction in Zanzibar Freddie Boswell from the BBC's African Service tells us about the former junkie who's helping others to get off drugs. New Australians Our reporter Sharon Mascall meets Esperance Kalonji, the clothes designer who fled the civil war in the Democratic Republic of Congo to make a new life in Brisbane. Death row artist Claire Phillips tells Matthew Bannister how she found the human face of death row through her art. Save our sounds And Dmitry Shishkin comes into the Outlook studio to tell us about the sounds that are being saved by Russian listeners to the BBC World Service. Show less